definition: head/chief/first (occasion, thing etc)/classifier for poems, songs etc
neck/collar/to lead/to receive/classifier for clothes, mats, screens etc

sentences.english: Madame Xian Tai was the chief of the Baiyue ethnic group in the Lingnan region.
sentences.chinese: 冼夫人是岭南百越族的一位首领。

sentences.english: But the mystique that surrounded the terrorist chieftain in life is persisting in death.
sentences.chinese: 但是围绕这位恐怖主义首领一生的谜团却并未解开。

sentences.english: The group was led by black ministers and the local leader of the Black Muslims.
sentences.chinese: 这个组织的领导人是黑人牧师和当地黑人穆斯林首领。

sentences.english: And he gathered together all the princes of Israel， with the priests and the Levites.
sentences.chinese: 大卫招聚以色列的众首领和祭司利未人。

sentences.english: And the prince of the tribe of the children of Naphtali, Pedahel the son of Ammihud.
sentences.chinese: 拿弗他利支派有一个首领，亚米忽的儿子比大黑。

sentences.english: This woman was named Lady Xian.
sentences.chinese: 这位女首领就是冼太夫人。

sentences.english: Yolande, what kind of business interests do army chiefs have?
sentences.chinese: 尤兰德，目前军界首领把控着哪些行业？

sentences.english: Cancels the cloud to wear and so on some fine jade is leader's accessories.
sentences.chinese: 勾云佩等一些精致的玉件是首领的饰品。

sentences.english: And for twenty-two years thereafter he served as the head of his stepmother’s armies.
sentences.chinese: 并且在之后的22年里，他都是自己继母的军队首领。

sentences.english: Allegiance to chiefs was a fundamental of Polynesian culture.
sentences.chinese: 效忠首领是波利尼西亚人最基本的文化。

sentences.english: Khan was a ruler under a well-developed regime in North Asia from the 4 th century on.
sentences.chinese: 可汗是四世纪以后北亚民族高级政治体首领的称谓。

sentences.english: QinLan advised Tian Zhengming must stay here to become a good leader.
sentences.chinese: 覃岚劝田正明必须要留下来，做一个好的首领。

sentences.english: The leaders of Israel and the king humbled themselves and said, 'The Lord is just.'
sentences.chinese: 于是王和以色列的众首领都自卑说，耶和华是公义的。

sentences.english: One felt that the chief of this barricade was a geometrician or a spectre.
sentences.chinese: 我们感到这个街垒的首领是一个几何学家或一个鬼怪。

sentences.english: Aguirre is now the ruler of a group of slowly starving, hallucinating men.
sentences.chinese: 阿基尔现在成了一群饱受饥饿与幻觉困扰者的首领。

sentences.english: He retorted, "Who made you chief and ruler over us?
sentences.chinese: 那人说“谁立你作我们的首领和审判官呢？

definition: headman (of primitive people)/tribal chief/used as translation for foreign leaders, e.g. Indian Rajah or Arab Sheik or Emir
